# Privacy Policy for AI Content Guardian

**Last Updated: January 15, 2026**

## Overview

AI Content Guardian ("we," "our," or "the extension") is committed to protecting your privacy. This Privacy Policy explains how we handle information when you use our browser extension.

**TL;DR: We don't collect, store, or transmit any of your personal data. Everything stays on your device.**

---

## Information We DO NOT Collect

AI Content Guardian does **NOT** collect, store, or transmit:

- ‚ùå Personal information (name, email, address, phone number)
- ‚ùå Browsing history or activity
- ‚ùå Content you analyze (text, images, URLs)
- ‚ùå Search queries or website visits
- ‚ùå Device information or identifiers
- ‚ùå Location data
- ‚ùå Cookies or tracking data
- ‚ùå Analytics or usage statistics
- ‚ùå Any data whatsoever

---

## How the Extension Works

### Free Mode (Default)

When you use AI Content Guardian in free mode:

1. **Local Processing**: All analysis happens locally in your browser
2. **Pattern Matching**: The extension uses pre-defined patterns stored in the extension itself
3. **No External Servers**: No data is sent anywhere
4. **Database Lookups**: Trusted site databases are stored locally in the extension
5. **Zero Data Collection**: Nothing leaves your device

### Pro Mode (Optional - User-Enabled)

If you choose to enable Pro Mode with your own API key:

1. **Your API Key**: Stored locally in your browser using Chrome's secure storage
2. **API Requests**: Content you analyze is sent to your chosen AI provider (Anthropic, OpenAI, or Google)
3. **Direct Connection**: Your browser connects directly to the AI provider - we never see or intercept this data
4. **Provider Privacy**: Subject to your AI provider's privacy policy (see below)
5. **Your Control**: You can disable Pro Mode or delete your API key at any time

---

## Data Storage

### What We Store Locally

The extension stores the following data **only on your device**:

- **Settings**: Your preferences (Pro Mode on/off, size preference)
- **API Key** (if Pro Mode enabled): Stored securely in Chrome's local storage, never transmitted to us
- **No Personal Data**: We never store any personal information

### How to Delete Your Data

1. Go to `chrome://extensions/`
2. Find "AI Content Guardian"
3. Click "Remove"
4. All local data is deleted

Or you can clear specific settings:
1. Open the extension popup
2. Go to Pro Mode tab
3. Clear your API key and disable Pro Mode

---

## Third-Party Services (Pro Mode Only)

### AI API Providers

If you enable Pro Mode, content you choose to analyze is sent to your selected AI provider:

**Anthropic (Claude)**
- Privacy Policy: https://www.anthropic.com/privacy
- You pay them directly for API usage
- Subject to their data retention and privacy practices

**OpenAI (GPT-4)**
- Privacy Policy: https://openai.com/privacy
- You pay them directly for API usage
- Subject to their data retention and privacy practices

**Google (Gemini)**
- Privacy Policy: https://policies.google.com/privacy
- You pay them directly for API usage
- Subject to their data retention and privacy practices

**Important:** We have no control over how these providers handle your data. Review their privacy policies before enabling Pro Mode.

---

## Permissions Explained

The extension requests the following Chrome permissions:

### `activeTab`
- **Why**: To analyze content on the page you're viewing
- **What it does**: Allows the extension to read page content when you explicitly request analysis
- **Privacy**: Only activates when you right-click and select "Check if AI-generated"

### `contextMenus`
- **Why**: To add right-click menu options
- **What it does**: Adds "Check if AI-generated" to your right-click menu
- **Privacy**: No data access

### `storage`
- **Why**: To save your settings (Pro Mode, size preference)
- **What it does**: Stores settings locally on your device
- **Privacy**: Never transmitted anywhere

### `scripting`
- **Why**: To display analysis results on pages
- **What it does**: Injects the results panel into the page you're viewing
- **Privacy**: Only activates when you request analysis

### `<all_urls>` (Host Permissions)
- **Why**: To analyze content on any website you choose
- **What it does**: Allows the extension to work on all websites
- **Privacy**: Only accesses pages when you explicitly use the extension

---

## No Tracking or Analytics

AI Content Guardian does **NOT** use:

- ‚ùå Google Analytics
- ‚ùå Facebook Pixel
- ‚ùå Any tracking scripts
- ‚ùå Cookies
- ‚ùå Telemetry
- ‚ùå Error reporting services
- ‚ùå Usage statistics

We have **no idea** how many people use the extension or how they use it. That's by design.

---

## No Advertisements

We do not display advertisements or sell your data to advertisers. The extension is supported through:

- ‚úÖ Optional donations (PayPal)
- ‚úÖ That's it

---

## Children's Privacy

AI Content Guardian does not knowingly collect information from children under 13 (or under 16 in the EU). The extension does not collect any personal information from anyone, regardless of age.

---

## International Users

The extension works entirely in your browser. No data crosses borders because no data is collected or transmitted (except in Pro Mode, where you communicate directly with your chosen AI provider).

---

## Data Security

Since we don't collect data, there's no data to secure. However:

- **API Keys**: If you use Pro Mode, your API key is stored securely in Chrome's encrypted local storage
- **Local Storage**: All settings use Chrome's secure storage APIs
- **HTTPS**: All external connections (Pro Mode API calls) use encrypted HTTPS

---

## Your Rights

Since we don't collect your data, you automatically have:

- ‚úÖ **Right to Privacy**: Maintained by default
- ‚úÖ **Right to Deletion**: Uninstall the extension
- ‚úÖ **Right to Access**: All data is on your device
- ‚úÖ **Right to Portability**: Export your settings (API key) anytime
- ‚úÖ **Right to Object**: Don't install the extension
- ‚úÖ **Right to Erasure**: Uninstall removes everything

---

## Open Source

AI Content Guardian's code can be inspected. The extension package contains all source code with no obfuscation. You can verify our privacy claims by reviewing the code yourself.

---

## Changes to This Privacy Policy

We may update this Privacy Policy from time to time. Changes will be posted with an updated "Last Updated" date. Continued use of the extension after changes constitutes acceptance of the updated policy.

However, our core commitment will never change: **We don't collect your data.**

